topics.body:
"@uc9":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/546a459f63687250b4060100#post_546a459f63687250b4060100
The C. 

In that context, the word would sound like "skent" if both letters made a sound. Take away the S, and it becomes "kent."

If the S was silent, it would still remain the "cent" sound. Take away the C, and it sounds like "sent." No change whatsoever.
